It’s holding forums across the nation as part of a push for immigration reform – at the very least, legal status for 1.8 million young people we call Dreamers.
The forum felt as bipartisan as the unsuccessful immigration reform efforts of the George W. Bush presidency.
If these folks were tasked with finding a workable immigration reform compromise, I thought, they could do it.
Silva shared the story of her grandfather, who came to the United States from Mexico under the bracero program (that’s the pull to the United States).
If Democrats care about Dreamers, they need to put what’s right above politics and work with the Koch brothers and congressional Republicans who are on the right side of this issue.